claim.claim-text:
11. A method of increasing flow dimension in an internal combustion engine comprising;
slidably attaching an auxiliary poppet valve to a valve stem of a main poppet valve such that a disc of the main poppet valve forms an air tight seal with a disc of the auxiliary poppet valve;
placing the attached auxiliary poppet valve and main poppet valve between an intake port tube and a combustion chamber of an internal combustion engine; and
placing an upper spring on a spring seat on an upper surface of an auxiliary poppet guiding member and placing a lower spring on a spring seat of a lower surface of the auxiliary poppet guiding member.
